  "texts": [
    "Prefix and prompt tuning are methods of adapting large pretrained language models to specific tasks or datasets with minimal updates to the model parameters.",
    "These techniques have gained prominence due to their efficiency and effectiveness, particularly in scenarios where updating the entire model is computationally expensive or impractical.",
    "Prefix tuning involves appending a sequence of tunable vectors, known as the prefix, to the input of each layer of the transformer model.",
    "Let us denote the transformer model as a function F that maps an input sequence x to an output y, i.e., y = F (x).",
    "In prefix tuning, this mapping is modified to y = F (p ⊕ x), where p represents the prefix and ⊕ denotes concatenation."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}